text.section:
An insurer shall issue a special endorsement only upon certification by the mortgagee that:
The residential property subject to the mortgage or rehabilitation loan is located within the boundaries of a neighborhood development zone established pursuant to KRS 99A.020;
The mortgagor is unable to secure the necessary funds for rehabilitation upon reasonable terms and conditions without the guaranty provided by the special endorsement;
The loan is an acceptable risk, taking into consideration the need for the rehabilitation, the security for the loan or loans, and the ability of the mortgagor to repay the mortgage or rehabilitation loan; and
The mortgage or rehabilitation loan transaction complies with such other terms, conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed by the executive director of the Kentucky Housing Corporation.
